  "name": "Nickel Laser Cleaning Dataset",
  "description": "Nickel stands out in laser cleaning applications thanks to its solid balance of reflectivity and absorptivity, which lets operators dial in precise energy absorption without excessive heat buildup. This sets it apart from more reactive metals by delivering clean finishes on tough surfaces like those in aerospace or chemical processing, while holding up against corrosion and thermal shock in demanding setups.",
